China ta sanar da karuwar sabbin kamuwa da cutar HIV/AIDS da kashi 14 cikin 100
China ta sanar da cewa yawan mutanen da ke da cutar HIV da AIDS ya karu zuwa kashi 14 cikin dari.
Jami'an kiwon lafiya sun ce fiye da mutane 820,000 ne suka kamu da cutar.
A cikin kwata na biyu na shekarar 2018 kadai, an samu sabbin mutane 40,000 da suka kamu da cutar.
Yawancin sabbin mutane da aka kama sun kasance masu jima'i ne, wanda ya canza daga shekarar da ta gabata.
Ya zuwa yanzu, ana yaduwar cutar HIV a wasu yankunan kasar Sin ta hanyar bayar da jinin da ke dauke da cutar ga mai lafiya.
Amma a wannan yanayin, an rage adadin masu kamuwa da cutar HIV zuwa kusan sifili, in ji babban jami'in kiwon lafiya na kasar Sin a lardin Yunnan.
Amma a duk shekara, mutane 100,000 ne ke rayuwa da cutar HIV a kasar Sin.
Cutar HIV ta hanyar jima'i babbar matsala ce ga al'ummar LGBT na kasar Sin.
A shekarar 1997, an sanya cin zarafin mata a matsayin laifi a kasar Sin, kuma ana ganin karuwar aikata laifuka ga LGBT a kasar Sin.
Bincike ya nuna cewa saboda al'adun gargajiya na kasar, kashi 70-90% na maza da suka yi jima'i da maza za su iya yin aure da mata.
Yawancin yaduwar cutar HIV saboda rashin kulawa da wadannan halayen.
Tun daga shekarar 2003, gwamnatin kasar Sin ta yi alkawarin samar da maganin cutar kanjamau a duk fadin kasar, a matsayin wani bangare na kokarin magance matsalar.
